# JavaScript Transition

## Basic

* Variables do not have a type, use `let`.
* You don't need `ArrayList`, try

```javascript
let coswave = [];

function setup() {
    createCanvas(720, 120);
    for (let i = 0; i < width; i++) {
        let amount = map(i, 0, width, 0, PI);
        coswave[i] = abs(cos(amount));
    }
    background(255);
    noLoop();
}

function draw() {
    let y1 = 0;
    let y2 = height;
    for (let i = 0; i < width; i += 3) {
        stroke(coswave[i] * 255);
        line(i, y1, i, y2);
    }
}
```

* you don't need class, try

```javascript
let bug;

function setup() {
    createCanvas(710, 400);
    bug = new Jitter();
}

function draw() {
    background(50, 89, 100);
    bug.move();
    bug.display();
}

class Jitter {
    constructor() {
        this.x = random(width);
        this.y = random(height);
        this.diameter = random(10, 30);
        this.speed = 1;
    }
    
    move() {
        this.x += random(-this.speed, this.speed);
        this.y += random(-this.speed, this.speed);
    }
    
    display() {
        ellipse(this.x, this.y, this.diameter, this.diameter);
    }
}
```
